replies.body:
It's not just that: later on you will have better access to blues, your core items, which give you a good pool, and in teamfights you wont need your w up for longer than 30s (and that if it's a long fight, considering you're somewhat bursty).

I can count on the fingers of one hand those instances where I desperately needed mana late game and it's an easy fix anyhow :)

Also, if you're ahead, pick up{{item:3285}} after {{item:3009}}

He's really good if you can get past how boring and awkward it is to play him. Most champions are able to deal a consistent amount of a damage without being completely shut down by someone walking **closer to them.**  He does very little early and you burn half your mana just to harrass {{sticker:zombie-brand-facepalm}}  

Champions like {{champion:238}} {{champion:84}} {{champion:157}} {{champion:98}} will give you an auerysm (noticing a trend here?) Pre 6 champions with any mobility will just harass you and you have nothing to deal with it. Taking {{summoner:3}}  or {{summoner:6}}  will help quite a bit as movement speed is basically a combat stat on him. In teamfights {{item:3116}}  will help you chunk and deal a suprising amount of damage without you even noticing. 
Taking MS quints and {{item:3009}} is a good idea if you want to be more consistent in fights. In Summary; he will be a complete dolt in the early game but late game you'll just start to melt entire teams and zone their carries.
